{"body": "I agree with @steveklabnik that this is unnecessary when it is just a `.map` call. If this is a common need for you, I'd reverse it and put the code on your `UserWrapper` so you do `UserWrapper.from User.where(:name => \"Bob\")` then you've got control over how it works and it's easier to understand because the primary noun (`UserWrapper`) is on the left.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/8390070", "created_at": "2012-09-08T16:21:36Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/7520#issuecomment-8390070", "updated_at": "2012-09-08T16:21:36Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 7520, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/evanphx/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/evanphx/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/evanphx/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/evanphx", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/evanphx/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/evanphx", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/evanphx/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/540cb3b3712ffe045113cb03bab616a2?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F8f14e45fceea167a5a36dedd4bea2543.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/evanphx/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/evanphx/received_events", "gravatar_id": "540cb3b3712ffe045113cb03bab616a2", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/evanphx/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "evanphx", "type": "User", "id": 7, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/evanphx/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "5237fac1bd3543c15100b6b2"}, "id": 8390070, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/7520"}
